      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="394e2aea-8246-4a43-b456-0621e5037ecf" type="Noun">
          <Vi>Bao thư</Vi>
          <En>A flat paper container used to enclose a letter or document, typically sealed and addressed.</En>
          <Example>She slipped the letter into the envelope and sealed it with a stamp.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="505101f3-a1e6-4c55-94b2-b0dd3b122f5f">
              <Vi>Việc viết thư tay và cho vào bao thư để gửi qua bưu điện.</Vi>
              <En>Writing a handwritten letter and placing it into an envelope for postal delivery.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="19b8eeb4-7be6-454c-94dd-eb491c175326">
              <Vi>Hộp thư điện tử (trong phần mềm) có tên cũng là envelope, mang nghĩa ẩn dụ.</Vi>
              <En>In email software, the term “envelope” refers metaphorically to the metadata (sender, recipient, subject), not the message body.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
